{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐπί-βᾰσις</b>, εως, ἡ, <br /> <b>stepping upon</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ἐς τὴν ναῦν 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Nav.” 12 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <b>advent,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Annuario 6/7.417 (from Phaselis); αἱ ἐ. τῆς θαλάσσης\">Refs</a>] <b>risings.. </b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 34.9.6. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3>. <b>means of</b> <b>approach, access</b>, ἔχειν ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“IG” 7.167 (from Megara); τοῦ νοητοῦ -σεις 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 6.7.36; ἐ. τοῦ ἐραστοῦ 4th c.AD: Themistius Sophista “Orationes” 13.163d \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]: hence concretely, <b>rungs, steps</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “R.” 511b (_plural_). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3>. ἔς τινα ποιεῖσθαι ἐ. make <b>a handle against, a</b> <b>means of attacking</b> one, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.61; ἐ. τι τίθεσθαι εἴς τι 2nd c.AD: Appianus Historicus “Bella Civilia” 1.37 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>attack</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Hist.Conscr.” 49; ἀμφισβητούμενον ἢ ἐπίβασιν ἔχον\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] liable <b>to</b> <b>be impugned</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“IG” 22.1051a14. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3>. <b>getting on one's feet</b>, of a child beginning to walk, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus 1.114; especially in recovery after a broken leg, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Fract.” 18 (_plural_); τῇ ἐ. χρῆσθαι [prev\\. author] “Art.” 58 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>foothold</b>, in snow, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.54.5. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3>. <b>resting of one thing on another</b>, e.g. of a bone, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 51. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__6</b></Level3>. Rhet., κατ᾽ ἐπίβασιν by <b>gradation</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Longinus Rhetor 11.1. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__7</b></Level3>. <b>that on which</b> <b>one stands</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 1.125, 332. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__8</b></Level3>. <b>entry</b> into office, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PLond.” 3.1170.3 (3rd c.AD). \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2>. of the male, <b>covering</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.754a(_plural_). \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7387","accentedUnicode":"ἐπίβασις","shortDef":"a step","mediumDef":"a step","stepGloss":"a step","stepTransliteration":"epibasis","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}